Brute Force: T.C. - O(N^2 * M) , S.C. - O(M) 

Approach : Two hashmaps Have(string s) and Need (string t) is there, its the occurence of the charachters in both the strings,
the game is HAVE = NEED , HAVE(CHAR) >= NEED(CHAR)

Imp points : In very sliding window question, the only approach is to calculate the occurence of the charachter, even if your
thinking denies it but go in that direction, the window length (j-i+1) is very imp + count.get(char, 0) very imp.

class Solution:
    def minWindow(self, s: str, t: str) -> str:
        if t == "":
            return ""

        countT = {}
        for c in t:
            countT[c] = 1 + countT.get(c,0)

        res, resLen = [-1,-1], float("infinity")

        for i in range(len(s)):
            countS = {}

            for j in range(i, len(s)):

                countS[s[j]] = 1 + countS.get(s[j],0)

                flag = True

                for c in countT:
                    if countT[c] > countS.get(c,0):
                        flag = False
                        break
                
                if flag and (j-i+1) < resLen:
                    res = [i,j]
                    resLen = (j-i+1)

        l,r = res
        return s[l:r+1] if resLen != float("infinity") else ""
        
